The Kali Puja is a major festival celebrated at the Kali Mandir temple on Kali Mandir Road in Bargarh. üéâ The festival honors the Goddess Maa Shyama Kali and is held during Diwali.

Yagyans, or fire sacrifices, are also performed as part of the festival.

The temple's main attraction is a large and beautiful statue of the Goddess Maa Shyama Kali, which is made from an alloy of eight metals.

A new temple for the Goddess was recently built, and it is a popular attraction for pilgrims. üö©

text.text: This is the famouse Sai Baba Temple of Bargarh. It is situated 2000meter ahead of Bhatli chowk and this place is very clean and beautiful. A small park is there and a Bhaban is there to organise different types of ceremoney like marriage,party,Badu and so on. Everyday 6pm on evening Aarti is given to Baba and for this so many people are visited there. Specially you find more people on Thursday. This day aftre puja a voga also given to all people present there or going for puja there. Sai Baba Birthday is also celebreat here every year and this is a very famouse and well known place of Bargarh city.
